        <h2 id="expect-title">The small details keep the page from feeling empty.</h2>
      </div>
      <article><span>01</span><h3>Short board</h3><p>Three to six lunch items, written as seasonal static copy the owner can swap each week.</p></article>
      <article><span>02</span><h3>Green table cues</h3><p>Photo-led patio, ingredient notes, and arrival context replace fake illustration-only ambience.</p></article>
      <article><span>03</span><h3>Visit boundary</h3><p>No ordering form or payment claim; the page routes menu questions to email and hours to the page.</p></article>
    </section>

